sentences.english: Objection to the jurisdiction is an important component of the jurisdiction system of civil litigation.
sentences.chinese: 管辖权异议制度是民事诉讼管辖制度的重要组成部分。

sentences.english: I have a problem with the fact that they just make really third-rate products.
sentences.chinese: 我持异议的是他们真的只做第三流的产品。

sentences.english: Do you have nay objection to the stipulations about the packing and shipping marks?
sentences.chinese: 有关包装运输唛头的条款你们有什幺异议吗？

sentences.english: And just below, there was a toll free number to call with disputes.
sentences.chinese: 就在那行字下面，有个反馈异议的免费号码。

sentences.english: One member of the commission dissented from the rest on two important matters.
sentences.chinese: 委员会中的一名在两件重大事情上与大伙产生异议。

sentences.english: With no enquiry, you are deemed to have fully understood the terms and conditions of this insurance contract.
sentences.chinese: 如未询问，则视同已经对合同内容完全理解并无异议。

sentences.english: Shine, and you cannot have any dissents.
sentences.chinese: 而你们不能有任何异议。

sentences.english: Mr. Diallo says he will contest the results.
sentences.chinese: 迪亚洛说，他将对选举结果提出异议。

sentences.english: Until today germanium is the present substance on earth with no exception.
sentences.chinese: 直至今天锗才毫无异议地成为地球上是纯净的物质。

sentences.english: He had made up his mind that Johnson was guilty, and he steamrollered anyone who disagree with him.
sentences.chinese: 他已经认定约翰逊有罪，并迫使任何持异议者就范。

sentences.english: I dissent altogether from such an unwise idea.
sentences.chinese: 我对这种不明智的意见全然持异议。

sentences.english: The whole contract has to be redrafted to take in the objection from the chairman.
sentences.chinese: 为了接受董事长的异议，整个合同都必须重新起草。

sentences.english: Here's the objection.It's a common enough objection.
sentences.chinese: 异议是这样的，是再常见不过的。

sentences.english: So we really have here two different objections to utilitarianism.
sentences.chinese: 因此我们确实对功利主义有两点异议。

sentences.english: The bonds between 2011's islands of youth dissent remain limited.
sentences.chinese: 2011年持异议的青年人岛屿之间的联系仍然有限。
持异议者主要担心两件事。
